abstract = {The aim of the paper is to assess the impact of the regulatory measure’s implementation on vehicles, based on real data of vehicles covering supplementation of chosen city center, especially with freight transport. The first chapter will deal with possible regulatory measures, which are meant especially low-emission zones, or noise reduction measures. Their implementation may affect carriers providing supplementation in the city center, given the need to operate vehicles with certain exhaust emission and noise limits in the area. Researching vehicles that currently provide transport services, we will also get an overview of their current status, particularly in terms of environmental impact. Especially good air quality is very important in areas with high pedestrian intensity at present. The paper also provides an answer, for example, to the question of what proportion of vehicles with a specified emission class would influence the implementation of a low-emission zone in the area. This would make it possible to quantify the costs for carriers in case of the regulatory measure’s implementation in the area and to try to find the optimum center between the economic costs of regulatory measures and the provision of supplementation of the area.}
